Interface TextFetchProgressListener

    • Method Detail

      • onStarted

        void onStarted()
        Indicates that the process of fetching characters from a Reader has started.

      • onProgress

        void onProgress(long charactersFetched)
        Indicates that the process of fetching characters from a Reader has progressed.

        The progress will only be reported if the TextFetcher is capable of monitoring the progress.

        Parameters:
        charactersFetched - Total amount of characters fetched so far.

      • onSuccedded

        void onSuccedded(Long charactersFetched)
        Indicates that the process of fetching characters from a Reader has succeeded.
        Parameters:
        charactersFetched - Total total amount of characters fetched or null, if the TextFetcher is not capable of monitoring the progress.

      • onFailed

        void onFailed(TextFetchException exception,
              Long charactersFetched)
        Indicates that the process of fetching characters from a Reader has failed.
        Parameters:
        exception - The TextFetchException that caused the process to fail. This is the same TextFetchException that is thrown in the failing method of TextFetcher that this TextFetchProgressListener has been given to.
        charactersFetched - Total total amount of characters fetched before the process failed or null, if the TextFetcher is not capable of monitoring the progress.

      • onFinished

        void onFinished()
        Indicates that the process of fetching characters from a Reader has finished.

        This method will be called after either onSuccedded(Long) or onFailed(TextFetchException, Long) has been called.
